The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, March 06, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, March 6, 2004				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Cheer Team India as it practises for the Pakistan tour at Eden Gardens on Sunday.				 																Movies and music				 																																	Celebrate Womens Day eve watching Mona Lisa Smile, starring Julia Roberts, at Inox, 10 am on Sunday. The special all womens pre-release screening has been organised by Inox in association with Womens Coordinating Council and Columbia Tristar Films.				 																																	Book your seats for the screening of The Hours, starring Stephen Daldry, at Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, 6 pm on Sunday.				 																																	Enjoy an evening of thumri-dadra bandish at Sangeet Research Academy, 6 pm on Sunday. Dr Malabika Mitra and her troupe will present Basant Bahar in Kathak.				 																Holi helpline				 																																	For any Holi-related emergency, call Apollo Gleneagles Hospitals Holi helplines  23585211/15, 9830202395. The service will be continued for a few days after Saturday.
